      "lineNbr": 1490,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T17:29:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "+1\n\nThe changes in FrameBuffer could be because you might be wondering how to pass through an existing post callback; I believe a way to do it without touching the existing FrameBuffer code is to communicate the post callback from android_setPostCallback to the screen recorder as well, and then reset the FrameBuffer\u0027s post callback when recording is enabled.\n\nAlso, why are there two calls to onPost here?",
      "parentUuid": "f89d8f11_cff69ab8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1482,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 1490,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "238c4274a37048a86d2d6c1ed1b9662762f846ce",
