      },
      "lineNbr": 1490,
      "author": {
        "id": 1128973
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T17:32:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I initially implemented it as another post callback, but the encoder was having issues dealing with the variable framerate since the post call only occurs when the frame is updated. I needed a way to get a consistent framerate, but didn\u0027t think implementing it here would make sense, so I did it in screen-recorder.cpp. That way, if screen-recorder wants x fps, it will just call getFrame() at x fps.",
      "parentUuid": "f89d8f11_cff69ab8",
